      "kwargs": {
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"success\":true,\"process_rule_id\":\"J09B\",\"process_rule\":\"1. Copy the decision table into table `J09B_temp` for all records where the tour starts with `J09B`.\\n\\n2. Add column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `J09B_temp`.\\n\\n3. Classify the meter reading type:\\n   - Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `KSA` when a `HAUS` has less than 3 `EQUNR`.\\n   - Else set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `EVU`.\\n   - Set all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1 = 0` to `EVU`.\\n\\n4. Join the table with `EABLG` using `INSTALLATION`.\\n\\n5. Join the table with `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER` using `EQUNR`.\\n\\n6. Compare customer sales master data and net master data.\\n\\n7. If sales customer data is not empty:\\n   1. Use the sales customer data table entries.\\n   Else:\\n   1. Use the net data customer table entries.\\n\\n8. Export the final table as CSV file named `J09B`.\\n   Use exactly these column names when exporting:\\n   `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\\n\\n9. Send an email to `meter.readings@evu.com` with the CSV file attached.\\n   Use `file_path: <path_to_exported_csv_file>`.\\n\\n10. Delete the temporary table.\\n\\n11. End the process.\"}",
            "id": "lc_789ba18f-685d-4954-af90-9ee5003788c1"
          }
        ],
        "type": "tool",
        "name": "retrieve_process",
        "id": "da8fb804-90d0-45ac-8525-341d326ea7ad",
        "tool_call_id": "call_CPc657HCqYPpRfCqnkD2SYlu",
        "artifact": {
          "structured_content": {
            "success": true,
            "process_rule_id": "J09B",
            "process_rule": "1. Copy the decision table into table `J09B_temp` for all records where the tour starts with `J09B`.\n\n2. Add column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `J09B_temp`.\n\n3. Classify the meter reading type:\n   - Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `KSA` when a `HAUS` has less than 3 `EQUNR`.\n   - Else set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `EVU`.\n   - Set all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1 = 0` to `EVU`.\n\n4. Join the table with `EABLG` using `INSTALLATION`.\n\n5. Join the table with `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER` using `EQUNR`.\n\n6. Compare customer sales master data and net master data.\n\n7. If sales customer data is not empty:\n   1. Use the sales customer data table entries.\n   Else:\n   1. Use the net data customer table entries.\n\n8. Export the final table as CSV file named `J09B`.\n   Use exactly these column names when exporting:\n   `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\n\n9. Send an email to `meter.readings@evu.com` with the CSV file attached.\n   Use `file_path: <path_to_exported_csv_file>`.\n\n10. Delete the temporary table.\n\n11. End the process."
          }
        },
        "status": "success"
      }
    },
